text: Their yuan yang smooth and not so sweet. Medium thickness. Affordable price at $1.  Overall 8/10.

You get traditional coffee and teh-o ka-tai here - and with a smile and prices of yesterday.

Yes, discovered them by accident. A pleasant surprise in this ulu west end of Singapore. Coffee is thick and aromatic.  Tea is fragrant and got oomph.  The ladies certainly know their business. Ever friendly unlike the grumpy uncle round the corner

Stall owners Mr. & Mrs. Heng are very friendly.
Vegetables bun & Siew mai  are the best I tried compared with other markets.

Their service is tip top, they can remember what I order when I was there the seconds timeüëÅ.

The owner is a very warm-hearted man.
